[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring class coverage**\n\nI'm thinking about class coverage in dynamic access and whether nested static classes are a real issue. It seems many tests make good use of them, so maybe it’s fine. However, I wonder if it’s possible to avoid using nested classes altogether and just stick with a top-level public class. That might simplify things, or at least make the structure a bit clearer. Let's see how that plays out!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ffa4e766892ee520169fd6b58d078819eb5d71e2137363cf7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_Wtq1QsvuirGJRPbdWeCr7lbfDLyyUMvqSQuSOxmk0ak4Q7VrRgmuayL-5N1LzvqfR0MmDW04yAukxDe82LxolCHIfxfzpcibfa8izutSrc-Gf4b797rgpbcUmhSPaB9gfOImqGnuN0IjqWhc9XEqaIjDy1waKY4FsZJ2KNBiqkRN6ZDHoTBh4_vv5-7He8i0EWCqdafkBwwDyxbb2WVuVsBeisKvxPlYKRxC4RDwiece_gVG0GSJgcmEQAIDvpkd8ZhLQVD7zVbNdCVvHfs23qPpOquvBE-HZq4OM6zUVge5GLpOqSa2CEQo4oOOErhozlU6a3QC-tPYoOqrl4jgHmYRSqYLiXWvDDTYK8PcQ5_lERgm-pCHRUKB7sndCeCjwoU3Sy7fpltUKMZADUn-KF9HLdHMbPQIMdcBvZsrqL0l9bKDFaD6Wl7P7vHZ0BfjA9zG0K1G4a7OkDIR7AakMyvKkrOVcxV3LPH_MI0ns0hj44RmGkreG-R5UTPI7xJoxvmmg8hoKuLkgAZOZ151PJxPaOoEZwFWME9zrDNk5jRcPzEFrpC5ShEa9r6so06dadhM9SvGkA0Iw7aGQQkNGRY3PDonol1sDN-wp8Y-mKrM96swLcFw2PqmKD2YCqAkECbrjpqxiw5VUNgxZ_myV2gzrCKYlWFJMcFSzMeh0xUoRvGHkQ1RGTZWLK6qpQaf7PSQlrc9ebrhUM-Ef0uzUy3jmwcQP98EThHtEktobhKy9NyxvV2Fv-mgYowMd2dcEcg4LcvfGXzzRLcNxy3rdNWWahTetQ4qTbr3xky1_bwYHOgu0MGrk1Y4QCmnKj13A0RvbNXFKKwPzXUhWHFOpHoSi65jI1PDPYGjtA0orWGAeDLw0p6rC8FOiKHnaedlmbXg0f1twKb_UXR2XDrSrBR88OoV8eZYVnqGdTWVfZGdsu18xmF487KSwmiNDLYAKXEkHfHy-yNr4LzBeTc7TFkeGGMdJv_fZy8U9f88VHdX42-Fg8mvLevTkARLzd1BX9foskB9tpLb5pBlyrhZROX3aA9_cQkTVGeShhmpuTnEw9ELZV5vzl3rZ2Zre5ZhgqhE1EOVZUFR8foEF1aVslSBC-3Zlca_RqnhPDxI1PE9NzI7Dh4LTzMbURI6adryu25PoUukhhr1furZqkALb2-ecoNS_NQ3TarfzIkfEu4iv8-3A_mxU8HrNoEEipKBPixEF9glgDyKroM3Pv_UBs4egw6ZOh2ebQKiLbNW9df2Rd8yhVhMwWZJ_YFtkxJ_WwB0RiWLH7QdWFQwShtFWZx7j86orqfk8w30pud