3\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test class visibility**\\n\\nI’m noticing a discrepancy in how developer guidance suggests all top-level test classes should be public, while older ones aren't. It seems I need to comply and ensure the public test structure. I wonder if helper classes should also be top-level. When referring to \\\"test classes,\\\" maybe it’s only those directly associated with tests. I think it’s fine to move forward and write the new file while removing the old one.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8KZx8EgNj0hZJqJC4CCBn80o|fc_0ffa4e766892ee520169fd6b6ed710819eaf19614b17f5a381", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.inject.extensions/guice-assistedinject/6.0.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject_extensions/guice_assistedinject/FactoryProviderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_google_inject_extensions.guice_assistedinject;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.google.inject.AbstractModule;\nimport com.google.inject.Guice;\nimport com.google.inject.Inject;\nimport com.google.inject.Injector;\nimport com.google.inject.Provider;\nimport com.google.inject.assistedinject.Assisted;\nimport com.google.inject.assistedinject.AssistedInject;\nimport com.google.inject.assistedinject.FactoryProvider;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\n@SuppressWarnings(\"deprecation\")\npublic class FactoryProviderTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsProxyForLegacyAssistedInjectConstructors() {\n        Injector injector = Guice.createInjector(new AbstractModule() {\n            @Override\n            protected void configure() {\n                bind(SuffixService.class).toInstance(new SuffixService(\"-legacy\"));\n                bind(MemberSuffix.class).toInstance(new MemberSuffix(\"/member\"));\n                bind(LegacyWidgetFactory.class).toProvider(\n                        FactoryProvider.newFactory(LegacyWidgetFactory.class, LegacyWidget.class));\n            }\n        });\n\n        LegacyWidgetFactory factory = injector.getInstance(LegacyWidgetFactory.class);\n        LegacyWidget widget = factory.create(\"widget\");\n\n        assertThat(widget.description()).isEqualTo(\"widget-legacy/member\");\n        assertThat(factory).isEqualTo(factory);\n        assertThat(factory.hashCode()).isEqualTo(System.identityHashCode(factory));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void inspectsFactoryMethodsWhenFallingBackToModernProvider() {\n        Provider<ModernWidgetFactory> provider =\n                FactoryProvider.newFactory(ModernWidgetFactory.class, ModernWidget.class);\n        Injector injector = Guice.createInjector(new AbstractModule() {\n            @Override\n            protected void configure() {\n                bind(SuffixService.class).toInstance(new SuffixService(\"-modern\"));\n                bind(ModernWidgetFactory.class).toProvider(provider);\n            }\n        });\n\n        ModernWidget widget = injector.getInstance(ModernWidgetFactory.class).create(\"widget\");\n\n        assertThat(widget.description()).isEqualTo(\"widget-modern\");\n    }\n}\n\ninterface LegacyWidgetFactory {\n    LegacyWidget create(String name);\n}\n\nfinal class LegacyWidget {\n    private final SuffixService suffixService;\n    private final String name;\n\n    @Inject\n    private MemberSuffix memberSuffix;\n\n    @AssistedInject\n    LegacyWidget(SuffixService suffixService, @Assisted String name) {\n        this.suffixService = suffixService;\n        this.name = name;\n    }\n\n    String description() {\n        return name + suffixService.value() + memberSuffix.value();\n    }\n}\n\ninterface ModernWidgetFactory {\n    ModernWidget create(String name);\n}\n\nfinal class ModernWidget {\n    private final SuffixService suffixService;\n    private final String name;\n\n    @Inject\n    ModernWidget(SuffixService suffixService, @Assisted String name) {\n        this.suffixService = suffixService;\n        this.name = name;\n    }\n\n    String description() {\n        return name + suffixService.value();\n    }\n}\n\nfinal class SuffixService {\n    private final String value;\n\n    SuffixService(String value) {\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n\n    String value() {\n        return value;\n    }\n}\n\nfinal class MemberSuffix {\n    private final String value;\n\n    MemberSuffix(String value) {\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n\n    String value() {\n        return value;\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3630, "output": 987, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23561, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778215787088, "responseId": "resp_0ffa4e766892ee520169fd6b6b8dec819ebe4b9e5ff85f9ed3"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8KZx8EgNj0hZJqJC4CCBn80o|fc_0ffa4e766892ee520169fd6b6ed710819eaf19614b17f5a381", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3675 bytes to tests/src/com.google.inject.extensions/guice-assistedinject/6.0.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject_extensions/guice_assistedinject/FactoryProviderTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778215794316}]}
